Air temp 80 degrees. Wind was from the west and was medium.  Beautiful day- saw 1 loon.
Nice day.  Temperature is 74 degrees.  Light winds from the east.  Saw 2 loons.
Very nice day.  Calm day.  Temperature 70 degrees.  Saw 1 loon.  Noticed that weeds were less and were receding from several shorelines.
44 degrees.  Clear blue skies.  Windy.  Saw 1 Eagle.  Lake had virtually no visible weeds on surface.
Observed that the entire lake had froze over.
Observed that most of Aldridge Lake had reopened due to unseasonably warm weather and heavy rains.

column1: Lake was observed again on December 24th as frozen over again.

column2: Temperature is 80 degrees- sunny- windy.  Winds out of the west.  No weeds present.  Saw 2 loons.
Nice clear day.  Sunny and 76 degrees- no wind.
68 degrees.  Partly cloudy- light winds.  Saw 1 loon and 1 heron.
Nice day.  Partly cloudy 55 degrees.  Calm winds.
4th of July week- lots of boat traffic for fishing- tubing- pleasure riding-  also jet ski traffic.  Nice day- 76- clear- breezy.
